Clean formulation

Your base system has:
	•	latent capacities
	•	stored traits
	•	learned weights
	•	modules
	•	heuristics

But those are like genes.

They are not always active.

What matters in runtime is the layer above them:

expression control

So the better model is:

Three layers

1. Genome layer

The full stored capability set.

In your system:
	•	user vectors
	•	item vectors
	•	governance weights
	•	reputation history
	•	modules
	•	traits
	•	rules

2. Epigenetic layer

The switches that decide what is turned on, suppressed, amplified, or damped.

In your system:
	•	context
	•	domain
	•	time pressure
	•	trust state
	•	emotional state proxy
	•	platform mode
	•	safety mode
	•	session history
	•	environmental triggers

3. Phenotype layer

The actual expressed runtime behavior.

In your system:
	•	recommendation
	•	ranking
	•	governance result
	•	visible output
	•	selected module path
	•	explanation style
	•	aggressiveness/conservatism of action

That is the real runtime stack.

Why this matters

Without this layer, a system is too static.

It says:
	•	user is type X
	•	source has score Y
	•	model weight is Z

But real systems behave more like:
	•	under uncertainty, express caution
	•	under trusted domain, express specialization
	•	under adversarial conditions, suppress risky modules
	•	under novelty hunger, amplify exploration
	•	under fatigue, reduce complexity
	•	under consensus collapse, increase invariant enforcement

That is exactly what epigenetics does as a metaphor:
it does not rewrite the underlying code every time,
it changes expression patterns.

The computational version

You could define:

expressed_state = f(base_state, environment, constraints, history)

Or more specifically:

module_activation = base_weight × context_multiplier × governance_gate × safety_gate

So a source or module may have high stored strength but low current expression.

Example:
	•	expert model has high expertise
	•	but low relevance in current domain
	•	therefore expression gets downweighted

Or:
	•	novelty engine is strong
	•	but current mode is safety-critical
	•	therefore exploration gets suppressed

